OL,3,CParents struggle to cope with their
OL,4,Cneurodiverse children's insomnia
OL,6,FThe couple wants to raise awareness of
OL,7,Fthe hidden effect neurodiversity can
OL,8,Fhave on families, adding that
OL,9,Femployers should be mindful of the
OL,10,Fimpact neurodiversity can have on
OL,11,Ftheir children's sleep schedule..
OL,13,FThe couple say they only experience
OL,14,Faround three hours of sleep a night
OL,15,Flooking after Lily, who suffers from
OL,16,Fdisturbed sleep despite medication.
OL,18,FHannah says: "I can't remember the
OL,19,Flast time we had a full night's sleep,
OL,20,Fas in a proper night's sleep.
