OL,3,CParents struggle to cope with their
OL,4,Cneurodiverse children's insomnia
OL,6,F"Even if my parents have her overnight
OL,7,Fto give us a break, we're so used to
OL,8,Fbeing woken up that we wake up and
OL,9,Fit's still a disturbed sleep. She
OL,10,Fslept better as a newborn."
OL,12,FChris and Hannah say their daughter's
OL,13,Finsomnia has affected their physical
OL,14,Fhealth, adding they suffer from
OL,15,Fstress, migraines, and poor
OL,16,Fconcentration which affects their day-
OL,17,Fto-day.
