OL,3,CParents struggle to cope with their
OL,4,Cneurodiverse children's insomnia
OL,6,FThe pair explains: "There's a greater
OL,7,Funderstanding of the child themselves
OL,8,Fbut is there an understanding of the
OL,9,Fimpacts on the parents? I don't know.
OL,11,F"I'm incredibly grateful that I get
OL,12,Ftime off to get her to her
OL,13,Fappointments or I'll text my boss and
OL,14,Ftell them I've had a rough night and I
OL,15,Fneed to come in a bit later today and
OL,16,Fhe understands but I don't know if
OL,17,Fother companies will be so accepting
OL,18,Fof it."
