OL,3,CParents struggle to cope with their
OL,4,Cneurodiverse children's insomnia
OL,6,FEvery evening, Lily takes melatonin
OL,7,Fwhich helps her regulate sleep cycles
OL,8,Fand circadian rhythms.
OL,10,FDespite this, Lily says she still
OL,11,Fstruggles with sleep and her
OL,12,Fnightmares have worsened.
OL,14,FLily says: "I can't lay on the side
OL,15,Fover to the way where my teddies are
OL,16,Fbecause I'm scared of looking over to
OL,17,Fthe way where there's a gap where my
OL,18,Fdoor is.
OL,20,F"I'm scared to even turn that way in
OL,21,Fcase... it really just scares me."
