OL,4,Cneurodiverse children's insomnia
OL,6,FITV News heard from other parents in
OL,7,FGuernsey whose neurodiverse children
OL,8,Fstruggle to sleep.
OL,10,FOne mother says: "When a bad night
OL,11,Farises, they hit like a freight train.
OL,12,FOur sleep situation has affected our
OL,13,Fability to work, our decisions about
OL,14,Fextending our family, (and) even our
OL,15,Fown relationship.
OL,17,F"You feel like a failure for letting
OL,18,Fit happen and being late to things
OL,19,Fbecause you're so tired."
